<TITLE> BNP amends constitution for registration </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)  The BNP's highest policy-making body approved a draft amendment to the party constitution on Sunday, ahead of registration with the Election Commission, said a senior party leader. Amid much speculation ahead of the EC deadline, the party had announced earlier Sunday it would be registering by the deadline of Monday. A BNP delegation had collected the registration form Sunday morning. BNP's decision to register was made to "safeguard the party", secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain told reporters at the time. BNP chief Khaleda Zia called an 'emergency meeting' at her Gulshan office to amend the party constitution for registration with the EC, office secretary Rizvi Ahmed had told bdnews24.com. Standing committee member RA Gani told bdnews24.com afterwards: "The standing committee has approved the party's new draft constitution." The committee sat for an hour and a half from 9pm, with the chairperson presiding. Among the other 11 standing committee members, M Saifur Rahman, Khandaker Delwar Hossain, Abdul Matin Chowdhury, RA Gani, Chowdhury Tanvir Ahmed Siddiqui, Khandaker Mahbubuddin, Mahbubur Rahman and M Shamsul Islam were present at the meeting. Two other members Dr Mosharraf Hossain and Moudud Ahmed are in detention. bdnews24
